25/01/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Top EU officials plan to discuss Kosovo with US President George W. Bush when he visits Brussels in February, Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn said Monday (24 January). He urged the Kosovo government and politicians to step up efforts to build "a democratic, multiethnic and tolerant society". 
In other news, Slavisa Petkovic, the head of a political group called Civilian Initiative Serbia, has agreed to join the Kosovo government as minister in charge of the return of refugees and communities. He has also taken one of the seats reserved for Serbs in the province's parliament. (Politika - 25/01/05; KosovaLive, AFP, Beta, B92, Tanjug - 24/01/05) 
